               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16881205-3-defend34" type="defendantName">
                     Peter 
                     Thomas
                  <interp inst="t16881205-3-defend34" type="surname" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-3-defend34" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-3-defend34" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was Tryed for <rs id="t16881205-3-off11" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16881205-3-off11" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-3-off11" type="offenceSubcategory" value="other"></interp>
               stealing a Watch from the person of 
                     
                        <persName id="t16881205-3-victim36" type="victimName">
                           Nathaniel 
                           Glover
                        <interp inst="t16881205-3-victim36" type="surname" value="Glover"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16881205-3-victim36" type="given" value="Nathaniel"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16881205-3-victim36" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-3-off11 t16881205-3-victim36"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , on the <rs id="t16881205-3-cd12" type="crimeDate">22d of October</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-3-off11 t16881205-3-cd12"></join> last
            </rs>: But upon Tryal it only appearing they were late drinking together, and that the Watch, of which no Demand was made in some days, might be elsewhere dropt, Glover having likewise inferred it in the Gazette as lost, and not stole, with the promise of a Reward to those that found and returned it and moreover, the Prisoner's Reputation appearing to be candid, he was <rs id="t16881205-3-verdict13" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16881205-3-verdict13" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
